While Isidingo gears to air its last episode this week, actress Katlego Danke has bagged a new gig. The star played Kgothalo in the long-running soapie before SABC's decision to can it. She is excited about the new chapter in her career while she has closed the one behind her. Taking to her Instagram account, the actress gushed about her new character, telling her followers not to miss it. The new show will also star Themba Ndaba, who is famously known as Uncle Brutus in Mzansi Magic's The Queen. It will premiere on 30 March on Mzansi Magic. Also read:Â KATLEGO DANKE PENS GOODBYE LETTER TO ISIDINGO